1
00:00:01,233 --> 00:00:04,536
     [grunting and groaning]

2
00:00:04,638 --> 00:00:09,508
       Scootaloo, is this
        such a... good idea?

3
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:11,143
What are you talking about?

4
00:00:11,345 --> 00:00:13,312
This is the best
idea I've ever had!

5
00:00:15,014 --> 00:00:16,248
           It's just--

6
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:19,051
--You wanna come. But
we talked about this.

7
00:00:19,253 --> 00:00:21,653
Non-Pegasus ponies fall
through the clouds.

8
00:00:24,124 --> 00:00:25,124
          Right, but--

9
00:00:26,126 --> 00:00:26,993
       I think we're good.

10
00:00:28,295 --> 00:00:29,195
             We are?

11
00:00:30,097 --> 00:00:32,431
      Scootaloo, I know you
    have to go to Cloudsdale

12
00:00:32,533 --> 00:00:34,600
     to finish your report;
       I'm just wondering

13
00:00:34,702 --> 00:00:36,902
       if this is the best
        way to get there.

14
00:00:37,304 --> 00:00:40,606
     It'll be fine. Besides,
   how else could I get there?

15
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:42,241
              A Pegasus chariot.

16
00:00:42,343 --> 00:00:43,509
A flock of birds!

17
00:00:43,611 --> 00:00:45,044
              A hot air balloon.

18
00:00:45,146 --> 00:00:47,813
 Huh, those do seem a lot safer.

19
00:00:48,215 --> 00:00:49,781
       Maybe I should try
        to find another--

20
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:52,449
           --WAAAAYY!

21
00:00:52,551 --> 00:00:54,553
               ♪♪

22
00:00:54,555 --> 00:00:55,554
             WOOHOO!

23
00:00:55,656 --> 00:00:59,158
               ♪♪

24
00:00:59,460 --> 00:01:00,192
             [grunt]

25
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,294
           Nailed it.

26
00:01:03,618 --> 00:01:04,218
[mower stops]

27
00:01:05,365 --> 00:01:07,299
        Little ma'am, are
         you all right?

28
00:01:08,123 --> 00:01:08,868
[shake]

29
00:01:09,469 --> 00:01:10,169
             [gasp]

30
00:01:10,271 --> 00:01:13,605
               ♪♪

31
00:01:13,607 --> 00:01:19,411
    You're-- you're-- you're
       Rainbow Dash's dad!

32
00:01:19,435 --> 00:01:21,180
♪♪

33
00:01:21,181 --> 00:01:23,916
       Ah yes. Bow Hothoof
        at your service.

34
00:01:25,685 --> 00:01:30,789
          [long shriek]

35
00:02:08,594 --> 00:02:11,663
     [long shriek continues]

36
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:14,900
     Uh, honey, something's
       going on out here!

37
00:02:14,924 --> 00:02:17,324
[long shriek continues]

38
00:02:17,348 --> 00:02:18,138
[shriek stops]

39
00:02:19,339 --> 00:02:21,774
        [higher shriek]

40
00:02:21,776 --> 00:02:25,211
Oh, heavens to Celestia,
what's wrong with her?!

41
00:02:25,813 --> 00:02:29,016
           I don't know, but you
            just made it worse.

42
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:30,517
[higher shriek continues]

43
00:02:30,518 --> 00:02:35,387
    Sorry, it's just, you're
     RAINBOW DASH'S PARENTS!

44
00:02:35,389 --> 00:02:38,357
          [long scream]

45
00:02:38,459 --> 00:02:39,958
           She's doing it again!

46
00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:41,827
              [shriek continues]

47
00:02:41,829 --> 00:02:43,227
       Oh, dearie, please.

48
00:02:43,329 --> 00:02:46,932
  You might shatter my Princess
 Celestia commemorative plates!

49
00:02:47,134 --> 00:02:47,766
              Agh!

50
00:02:47,768 --> 00:02:49,368
       [scream continues]

51
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:50,536
            [shatter]

52
00:02:51,060 --> 00:02:51,637
[scream stops]

53
00:02:52,138 --> 00:02:55,908
    I'm so sorry. I just... I
 can't believe I'm meeting you.

54
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:58,076
     My name's Scootaloo and
    I'm doing a school report

55
00:02:58,178 --> 00:02:59,244
        on your daughter.

56
00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:01,947
Our Rainbow Dash?

57
00:03:02,449 --> 00:03:04,783
       The report's on an
 inspirational pony in my life.

58
00:03:04,785 --> 00:03:07,352
      And no pony inspires
     me more than she does!

59
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:11,690
    I'm putting together this
    scrapbook for my report.

60
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:13,859
      I'm her biggest fan!

61
00:03:14,461 --> 00:03:17,796
      Little trotter, what
    you say is impossible...

62
00:03:17,898 --> 00:03:23,168
 because nopony is a bigger fan
  of our Rainbow Dash THAN US!

63
00:03:25,238 --> 00:03:29,275
        Whoa. You always
        wear that shirt?

64
00:03:29,777 --> 00:03:33,745
Actually it's er.. laundry day,
but pretty great, right?

65
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:34,680
                Yeah!

66
00:03:35,382 --> 00:03:38,350
        My name's Windy Whistles
         and I just have to say

67
00:03:38,352 --> 00:03:40,719
            that it is a total
          blast to meet somepony

68
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:43,889
            that loves Rainbow
          Dash as much as we do!

69
00:03:43,991 --> 00:03:45,389
What can we help
    you with?

70
00:03:45,591 --> 00:03:48,493
 Well, I know all about Rainbow
    Dash's time in Ponyville,

71
00:03:48,495 --> 00:03:50,863
    but I don't know anything
   about her life before that.

72
00:03:51,365 --> 00:03:53,999
Well, you came to
the right place.

73
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:54,968
[camera snap]

74
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,469
[delighted gasp]

75
00:03:59,339 --> 00:04:02,408
   Windy: Here you go. Rainbow
      Dash's favorite meal.

76
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:06,245
       A pasta and potato
     sandwich on sourdough!

77
00:04:06,547 --> 00:04:08,114
  She just LOVES to carbo load!

78
00:04:09,016 --> 00:04:12,351
I can't believe I'm eating
Rainbow Dash's favorite food,

79
00:04:12,553 --> 00:04:14,720
made by Rainbow Dash's mom,

80
00:04:14,822 --> 00:04:18,023
while sitting in Rainbow
Dash's childhood kitchen!!

81
00:04:18,325 --> 00:04:21,894
This is the greatest
day of my life!

82
00:04:22,596 --> 00:04:23,328
[chomp]

83
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:25,197
[munching]

84
00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:27,399
Mm! Mmmmm!

85
00:04:27,801 --> 00:04:30,836
I think it's time for
a tour of the house.

86
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:32,171
               OK!

87
00:04:32,873 --> 00:04:36,875
  Our little Dashie was an early
  learner and so rambunctious.

88
00:04:38,711 --> 00:04:40,211
     The combination was...

89
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,413
            EXCITING!

90
00:04:42,337 --> 00:04:43,037
[camera snap]

91
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:46,285
              Woah.

92
00:04:46,387 --> 00:04:51,456
               ♪♪

93
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:53,358
               Is that her room?

94
00:04:53,382 --> 00:04:55,882
♪♪

95
00:04:55,895 --> 00:04:58,096
                        [scream]

96
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:01,000
  Rainbow Dash's linen closet!

97
00:05:01,702 --> 00:05:03,102
           Her carpet!

98
00:05:03,504 --> 00:05:05,638
    Her inspirational poster!

99
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:09,474
   "When the going gets tough,
     the tough don't notice

100
00:05:09,576 --> 00:05:13,478
 because they have hard shells."
     That's so Rainbow Dash.

101
00:05:14,402 --> 00:05:14,802
[camera snap]

102
00:05:15,326 --> 00:05:15,726
[camera snap]

103
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:16,550
[camera snap]

104
00:05:18,017 --> 00:05:19,318
             Woohoo!

105
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:22,721
Scootaloo, want to see
something really cool?

106
00:05:25,145 --> 00:05:25,845
[curtains open]

107
00:05:27,269 --> 00:05:27,826
[door opens]

108
00:05:27,927 --> 00:05:35,400
      <i> ♪ [angelic choir] ♪</i>

109
00:05:35,402 --> 00:05:36,601
             [gasp]

110
00:05:36,603 --> 00:05:40,172
               ♪♪

111
00:05:40,374 --> 00:05:41,172
 [door closes/angel choir ends]

112
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:44,343
         I.. uhh.. installed the
          sound effects myself.

113
00:05:44,645 --> 00:05:46,845
              [door opens/closes]
              [choir starts/ends]

114
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:48,147
Pretty great, huh?

115
00:05:48,449 --> 00:05:49,615
                       So great!

116
00:05:49,717 --> 00:05:51,016
And look at this.

117
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:54,787
     She was wearing it when
   she spoke her first words.

118
00:05:55,589 --> 00:05:57,422
            So cool!

119
00:05:58,046 --> 00:05:58,446
[camera snap]

120
00:05:59,926 --> 00:06:03,562
And this broken lantern is from
when she first learned to fly.

121
00:06:04,486 --> 00:06:04,886
[camera snap]

122
00:06:05,665 --> 00:06:09,569
And this bitten apple is from
when she grew her first tooth.

123
00:06:10,671 --> 00:06:12,003
So many memories...

124
00:06:12,427 --> 00:06:12,827
[camera snap]

125
00:06:13,139 --> 00:06:16,041
       You're so lucky to
       have all of these.

126
00:06:16,343 --> 00:06:18,877
       Well, I may have a
       ton of Dash-mentos,

127
00:06:19,079 --> 00:06:20,779
                but I don't have
                  any of those

128
00:06:20,881 --> 00:06:24,416
    Rainbow Dash saves Ponyville
         headlines like you.

129
00:06:24,818 --> 00:06:26,168
[gasp!] Tradesies?

130
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:27,285
                       Dealsies!

131
00:06:27,609 --> 00:06:27,909
[bump]

132
00:06:30,709 --> 00:06:31,009
[bump]

133
00:06:31,457 --> 00:06:33,759
So where's all the
 Wonderbolt stuff?

134
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:37,796
         You mean.. Rainbow Dash's
           personal collection

135
00:06:37,798 --> 00:06:39,499
      of Wonderbolt memorabilia?

136
00:06:40,501 --> 00:06:43,001
   No, I mean where's all the
    stuff about Rainbow Dash

137
00:06:43,103 --> 00:06:45,270
      getting accepted into
     the Wonderbolt Academy

138
00:06:45,472 --> 00:06:47,572
        and then getting
     chosen as a Wonderbolt.

139
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:52,744
Wait, you don't know that
your daughter's a Wonderbolt?

140
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,147
And I got to tell you!

141
00:06:56,271 --> 00:06:57,871
[huge gasp!]

142
00:06:57,984 --> 00:07:01,119
     Oh, wow, you should see
      your faces right now!

143
00:07:01,843 --> 00:07:02,243
[camera snap]

144
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:05,457
See that's what your
faces look like.

145
00:07:05,581 --> 00:07:07,981
♪♪

146
00:07:10,997 --> 00:07:13,566
  Our daughter's a WONDERBOLT?!

147
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:16,668
       <i> ♪ [angel choir] ♪</i>

148
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:17,302
          [door closes]

149
00:07:17,704 --> 00:07:18,637
          Great timing.

150
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:19,871
           Great door.

151
00:07:19,873 --> 00:07:23,709
  I just... it's unbelievable!

152
00:07:24,111 --> 00:07:27,279
You two were kind enough to show
  me the Rainbow Dash you know;

153
00:07:27,581 --> 00:07:31,350
  now please, allow me to show
  you the Rainbow Dash I know.

154
00:07:31,552 --> 00:07:41,459
               ♪♪

155
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:42,961
        Let's make some thunder!

156
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:45,096
I was born to
make thunder!

157
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,665
♪♪

158
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:47,866
[thunderclap]

159
00:07:48,568 --> 00:07:49,567
           [shouting]

160
00:07:49,669 --> 00:07:51,036
      We've got turbulence!

161
00:07:51,038 --> 00:07:53,071
How? Where's it
coming from?

162
00:07:53,073 --> 00:07:54,206
[shouting]

163
00:07:54,408 --> 00:07:55,306
                        There!

164
00:07:55,308 --> 00:08:00,278
            [encouraging shouts]

165
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:01,480
             Oh, no.

166
00:08:03,649 --> 00:08:05,849
OK, which pony
broke protocol

167
00:08:05,886 --> 00:08:08,620
and invited guests to
our training exercises?

168
00:08:09,122 --> 00:08:10,822
                I guess they're
                   with me.

169
00:08:11,424 --> 00:08:12,324
                Agh!

170
00:08:14,094 --> 00:08:18,764
               Mom, Dad,
                 so ..good to see you.

171
00:08:18,966 --> 00:08:22,101
        Oh, honey it's so
     great to see you, too!

172
00:08:22,903 --> 00:08:25,570
And WOW! You were so
amazing up there

173
00:08:25,572 --> 00:08:27,372
with all of that flying!

174
00:08:27,574 --> 00:08:29,708
                Er.. How did you know
                   I was here?

175
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:32,844
Scootaloo filled us
in on everything.

176
00:08:32,946 --> 00:08:35,013
You modest pony, you.

177
00:08:36,137 --> 00:08:36,737
[camera snap]

178
00:08:37,617 --> 00:08:40,185
       I can't believe I'm
     documenting the moment

179
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:42,854
     your parents first saw
      you as a Wonderbolt!

180
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:47,827
          And these must be your
            Wonderbolt friends.

181
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:52,364
 Hello team! I'm Windy Whistles,

182
00:08:52,766 --> 00:08:56,802
the mom of the best
Wonderbolt ever! Yeah!

183
00:08:57,404 --> 00:09:00,639
Just kidding.. you guys
were great, too. Go team!

184
00:09:01,041 --> 00:09:02,540
              Mom....

185
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:03,742
[laugh]

186
00:09:03,844 --> 00:09:06,311
               Hello Ma'am, nice
                 to meet you.

187
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:11,850
Nice to meet you, as well and
love those goggles! Love 'em!

188
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:14,519
You know I have
goggles, too,

189
00:09:14,821 --> 00:09:17,689
but they're mostly just for
swimming. Oh and bath time.

190
00:09:19,158 --> 00:09:23,428
Mom, please! They don't want
to hear about your bath time.

191
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:27,166
I can't believe it. My
daughter, a Wonderbolt!

192
00:09:28,168 --> 00:09:29,401
            So proud!

193
00:09:29,903 --> 00:09:33,038
     Dad, hold it together!
        We're in public.

194
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:35,540
I know, I know, but it's just...

195
00:09:35,642 --> 00:09:38,510
       you had a goal and
        ...you achieved it!

196
00:09:38,912 --> 00:09:42,914
          [blubbering]

197
00:09:43,438 --> 00:09:43,916
[camera snap]

198
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,067
     All right Wonderbolts,
      let's hit the showers

199
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:50,656
   and give Rainbow Dash some
 time to spend with her family.

200
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:54,025
    OK, yeah. Great practice.

201
00:09:54,127 --> 00:09:56,696
     I'll uh, catch up with
      you guys in a minute.

202
00:09:57,598 --> 00:09:59,866
Sir. You really
raised a great flyer.

203
00:10:01,368 --> 00:10:05,536
         Oh, no... tears
        welling up again!

204
00:10:05,638 --> 00:10:06,738
              Dad.....

205
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:12,140
[blubbering]

206
00:10:12,245 --> 00:10:12,745
[camera snap]

207
00:10:13,146 --> 00:10:14,546
        Could you give us a sec?

208
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:17,149
Is something wrong?

209
00:10:17,551 --> 00:10:19,084
        Yeah, you should
         have warned me

210
00:10:19,186 --> 00:10:20,784
          that you were
      bringing my parents,

211
00:10:20,886 --> 00:10:23,555
    or talked to Twilight or
  something. Not just shown up!

212
00:10:24,257 --> 00:10:25,055
              Why?

213
00:10:25,757 --> 00:10:28,927
   It's just, my parents and I
  have a delicate relationship.

214
00:10:29,029 --> 00:10:31,196
      I love them very much
     and we're really close,

215
00:10:31,298 --> 00:10:34,032
  but there's a reason I didn't
   tell them I'm a Wonderbolt!

216
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:37,002
      They can be a little
        bit... embarrassing.

217
00:10:37,404 --> 00:10:40,205
          Huh...? Really?

218
00:10:40,707 --> 00:10:42,074
          Yeah, really.

219
00:10:42,376 --> 00:10:45,778
 And now you've invited a whole
   lot of crazy into my life!

220
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,713
        What's wrong with
        a little support?

221
00:10:50,683 --> 00:10:53,885
               ♪♪

222
00:10:53,887 --> 00:10:56,054
Bow and Windy, I'd
like you to meet

223
00:10:56,056 --> 00:10:57,522
Apple Bloom and
Sweetie Belle.

224
00:10:57,724 --> 00:10:58,374
          Hi!

225
00:10:58,391 --> 00:10:59,090
               Hello!

226
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,792
Greetings, small ponies.

227
00:11:01,394 --> 00:11:03,194
Are you excited to
see Rainbow Dash?

228
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:05,264
          Oh, my, YES!

229
00:11:05,666 --> 00:11:09,100
 And to think we never bothered
 to come to a Wonderbolt event!

230
00:11:09,302 --> 00:11:11,303
     We said if Rainbow Dash
       isn't a Wonderbolt,

231
00:11:11,405 --> 00:11:14,273
         then what's the
     point? But now she is!

232
00:11:14,775 --> 00:11:16,241
       And she earned it!

233
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:20,211
       Did you know it all
   started when she won a spot

234
00:11:20,313 --> 00:11:22,647
         in the coveted
       Wonderbolt Academy,

235
00:11:22,749 --> 00:11:24,683
    training under Spitfire!

236
00:11:25,085 --> 00:11:28,753
       I didn't know that!
         How wonderful!

237
00:11:29,155 --> 00:11:31,790
      But then she had some
       heavy competition,

238
00:11:31,992 --> 00:11:35,860
   especially against another
  Pegasus named Lightning Dust.

239
00:11:36,162 --> 00:11:37,796
    Oh, no...

240
00:11:37,998 --> 00:11:40,632
But of course, Rainbow
Dash proved to be the best

241
00:11:40,834 --> 00:11:43,568
     and later made it into
    the Wonderbolt Reserves!

242
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:45,637
          Hooray again!

243
00:11:45,939 --> 00:11:49,941
But.. a jealous ex-Wonderbolt,
Wind Rider, was worried

244
00:11:50,043 --> 00:11:52,877
that Rainbow Dash might
break his speed record

245
00:11:52,979 --> 00:11:57,048
and so he framed her for
a crime she didn't commit.

246
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:59,200
     Oh, no!

247
00:11:59,753 --> 00:12:02,754
But thanks to Rarity, Rainbow
Dash proved her innocence

248
00:12:02,756 --> 00:12:04,723
and became a back-up Wonderbolt.

249
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,825
    Until Fire Streak retired

250
00:12:06,927 --> 00:12:09,294
        and she became an
      official Wonderbolt!

251
00:12:09,796 --> 00:12:11,062
                  Hooray!

252
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:14,299
   Wow! What a gripping tale.

253
00:12:14,601 --> 00:12:16,851
           You really know your
           Rainbow Dash history.

254
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:19,203
       You're going to do
      great on your report.

255
00:12:20,706 --> 00:12:21,806
     Show's about to start!

256
00:12:23,275 --> 00:12:26,377
               ♪♪

257
