00:16:59,085 --> 00:17:05,924
       Yeah! Rainbow Dash,
         you show them!

346
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,961
   Greatest participant ever!

347
00:17:09,263 --> 00:17:12,497
   Uh... your parents realize you
     didn't win, don't they?

348
00:17:14,821 --> 00:17:15,321
[camera snap]

349
00:17:15,401 --> 00:17:18,169
Granted, I was the youngest pony

350
00:17:18,271 --> 00:17:20,138
          in the senior
      competitive circuit.

351
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:21,806
    Most other ponies my age

352
00:17:21,808 --> 00:17:24,142
        were still in the
      junior flappers club.

353
00:17:24,744 --> 00:17:27,245
        I thought it was
       utterly mortifying

354
00:17:27,347 --> 00:17:30,015
     having my parents cheer
     me on even when I lost.

355
00:17:30,717 --> 00:17:33,218
     But then when I started
      to win competitions,

356
00:17:33,420 --> 00:17:35,487
        which didn't take
     very long, by the way,

357
00:17:35,789 --> 00:17:37,923
     things got even worse.

358
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:42,593
     Woo!! Yeah! Go Rainbow!
       Go Rainbow! Woohoo!

359
00:17:42,695 --> 00:17:45,463
     Yeah, Rainbow Dash! You
    show em! That's our girl!

360
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:47,532
       Being the best came
       with consequences.

361
00:17:47,734 --> 00:17:51,102
         Very loud, very
   embarrassing consequences.

362
00:17:52,404 --> 00:17:53,303
                    [sigh]

363
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,973
You know, some
ponies would dream

364
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:57,575
of having parents
like that.

365
00:17:57,710 --> 00:17:59,379
          Yeah, right, name one.

366
00:18:00,103 --> 00:18:00,680
[sigh]

367
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:06,184
 Me. Growing up, I never thought
   I'd be the best at anything

368
00:18:06,286 --> 00:18:08,287
  because no pony ever told me.

369
00:18:08,789 --> 00:18:12,257
    But your parents told you
  over and over again -- look.

370
00:18:12,859 --> 00:18:17,462
   Best bath taker ever. Best
    carrot eater under three.

371
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:20,532
  Greatest napper of all time!

372
00:18:21,434 --> 00:18:25,036
  I am pretty good at napping.
   I can fall asleep anywhere.

373
00:18:25,538 --> 00:18:28,673
            [snoring]

374
00:18:28,975 --> 00:18:29,574
              Huh?

375
00:18:30,976 --> 00:18:33,411
For your entire life,
your parents gave you

376
00:18:33,513 --> 00:18:35,446
the confidence to
believe in yourself.

377
00:18:35,570 --> 00:18:39,370
 ♪♪

378
00:18:39,551 --> 00:18:43,688
   You're right. I was always
  so embarrassed by my parents

379
00:18:43,890 --> 00:18:46,657
   that I didn't realize their
    support actually made me

380
00:18:46,759 --> 00:18:49,727
     the awesome, confident,
        amazing, awesome

381
00:18:49,829 --> 00:18:51,762
     and awesome pony I am!

382
00:18:55,033 --> 00:18:57,069
  And I took them for granted!

